}}{{Quote|Man once again faces [[The Long Night|the war for the dawn]], which has been waged since time began. On one side is the Lord of Light, the Heart of Fire, the God of Flame and Shadow. Against him stands the Great Other, whose name may not be spoken. The Lord of Darkness, the Soul of Ice, the God of Night and Terror.|[[Thoros of Myr]]|The Lord of Light (Histories &amp; Lore)}}
The '''Great Other''' is the god of darkness, cold, evil, fear and death in the faith of [[R'hllor]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Lord of Light (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Lion and the Rose]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
